# Code ownership — auto-request review from the repository owner
# on every pull request, regardless of which paths it touches.
#
# GitHub matches the *last* line for any given path, so the
# catch-all entry below covers everything. Add narrower rules
# above this line if you ever want to delegate specific paths to
# additional reviewers (e.g. `/docs/  @docs-team`).
#
# How this enforces "only the owner reviews and merges":
#
#   1. CODEOWNERS makes the owner an automatic *requested*
#      reviewer on every PR — visible signal in the PR sidebar.
#   2. Branch protection (see `.github/setup-branch-protection.sh`)
#      pairs this with `require_code_owner_reviews = true` so the
#      owner's approval is the path to merge once any other
#      collaborator submits a PR.
#   3. As a personal-account public repo, only the owner has
#      `write` permission by default — outside contributors fork
#      and PR; only the owner can click *Merge*.
#
# That's the maximum enforcement GitHub allows for a solo-dev
# public project; together they cover the "I'm the only one who
# can review and merge code" requirement.

